  "prompt": "What materials are used for road construction?",
  "response": "Several materials are commonly used in road construction:\n\n1. Asphalt\n- Most common road surface material\n- Made from bitumen and aggregate stones\n- Flexible and durable\n\n2. Concrete\n- Used for highways and heavy-traffic roads\n- Composed of cement, water, and aggregates\n- Very strong and long-lasting\n\n3. Aggregates\n- Crushed stone\n- Gravel\n- Sand\n- Used in base and surface layers\n\n4. Subbase materials\n- Crushed rock\n- Recycled concrete\n- Provides foundation and drainage\n\n5. Gravel\n- Used in road base layers\n- Provides stability and drainage\n\n6. Recycled materials\n- Recycled plastic\n- Recycled concrete\n- Rubber from tires\n- Increasingly used for sustainability\n\n7. Stabilizing agents\n- Lime\n- Cement\n- Improve soil strength and durability\n\n8. Geotextiles\n- Synthetic fabrics\n- Provide reinforcement and separation of layers\n\n9. Steel reinforcement\n- Used in concrete roads\n- Increases strength and reduces cracking\n\nThese materials are selected based on factors like traffic volume, climate, and local resources.",
